scoringPlays.text: Hunter Bryant 11 Yd pass from Jake Browning (Tristan Vizcaino Kick)
Jake Browning 21 Yd Run (Van Soderberg Kick)
Myles Gaskin 8 Yd Run (Van Soderberg Kick)
Jusstis Warren 2 Yd pass from Jake Browning (Van Soderberg Kick)
Darius Allensworth 37 Yd Fumble Return (Matt Anderson Kick)
Myles Gaskin 7 Yd Run (Van Soderberg Kick)

videos.description: Jake Browning rolls right and throws to Hunter Bryant in the end zone.  Bryant catches the pass at the same time as a Cal defender, but by rule, the offense is awarded with the catch, resulting in an 11-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Washington scores TD on simultaneous catch in end zone

videos.description: On fourth down, Jake Browning keeps the ball himself and scampers into the end zone for a 21-yard touchdown, giving the Huskies a 17-0 lead.
videos.headline: Washington QB Browning uses his legs to score on fourth down

videos.description: Myles Gaskin takes a handoff, jukes a defender, and easily scores from eight yards out to give Washington a 24-0 first-half lead.
videos.headline: Gaskin reaches end zone untouched for Huskies TD

videos.description: Washington coach Chris Petersen says his team has controlled the line of scrimmage in the first half, but says they need to do a better job of converting in the red zone in the second half.
videos.headline: Petersen pleased with Huskies' first-half performance

videos.description: After accumulating just 46 yards in the first half, Cal WR Jeremiah Hawkins drops a potential touchdown in the Golden Bears' opening drive of the second half.
videos.headline: Cal's offensive woes continue with dropped pass

videos.description: Jake Browning fakes a handoff to the running back and gets the defense to commit before rolling right and finding Jusstis Warren wide-open for a 2-yard touchdown, extending the Huskies' lead to 31-0.
videos.headline: Washington fools defense, scores TD on play-action pass

videos.description: Dante Pettis catches a pass then fumbles, and Darius Allensworth recovers the ball and returns it back 37 yards to score Cal's first points of the game.
videos.headline: Golden Bears scoop and score for defensive TD

videos.description: Myles Gaskin finds a seam in the defense and dives into the end zone for a 7-yard touchdown run, giving the Huskies a 38-7 lead.
videos.headline: Gaskin's second TD extends Washington's lead

videos.description: Washington QB Jake Browning says the defense made it easy on the offense tonight, but says the offense has some areas to clean up going forward.
videos.headline: Browning: 'Dominant' defense key to victory

videos.description: Rod Gilmore and Mark Jones break down Washington's 38-7 win over California, crediting the Huskies' dominant defense and efficient offense as the reasons for the blowout win.
videos.headline: Washington shows its defense is 'best in the Pac-12' in win over Cal
